Our story
Privacy Policy
Last Updated:
Nov 15, 2024
1. Introduction
Swipefy B.V. ("we," "us," "our") is committed to protecting your privacy. This Privacy Policy explains how we collect, use, and share your personal information when you use our mobile application, Swipefy, in compliance with the General Data Protection Regulation (GDPR), California Consumer Privacy Act (CCPA), UK Data Protection Act 2018, and other applicable laws, including compliance with Apple's App Store Guidelines.
2. Information We Collect
2.1. Account Information
Spotify/Apple Music Account Information:
When you sign in using your Apple ID or Spotify account, we collect basic account information, including your username, email address, and playlist data.
2.2. User-Generated Data
Profile Information:
We collect and store your profile picture, username, and email address.
Swipe Data:
We record your likes and dislikes based on your interactions with music recommendations.
Playlist Information:
We collect information about your playlists, including track content, name, image, and description.
2.3. Usage Data
Analytics Data:
We use Firebase Analytics to collect information about how you use the app, including which features you use and how often.
Consumption Data:
We collect data about your Pro features consumption to provide personalized features and recommendations. With your explicit consent, we may share this data with Apple in compliance with their guidelines. This includes playback history and usage trends as outlined in the Apple Developer Documentation.
3. How We Use Your Information
We use your information to:
Provide personalized music recommendations
Facilitate the functioning of your account and app experience
Enhance and improve Swipefy’s features
Communicate with you about updates, promotions, and your account
Fulfill compliance requirements with App Store guidelines, including the lawful sharing of consumption data upon your consent.
Your data will only be processed where we have a lawful basis to do so under GDPR, CCPA, and other applicable laws.
4. Data Storage
Your data is stored in secure data centers located in Germany, managed in compliance with GDPR. We implement industry-standard measures to protect your data from unauthorized access, alteration, or destruction.
5. Sharing Your Information
With your explicit consent, we may share consumption data, as defined by Apple, with Apple to comply with App Store guidelines and facilitate app functionalities. This sharing will only occur if you have opted in during the account setup or via app settings.
Additionally, we may provide anonymized insights into user data and trends to third parties. These insights will not include any personally identifiable information and will comply with applicable privacy laws.
6. Advertising
Free users of Swipefy will see advertisements, including Google Ads and custom music advertisements. These ads may be personalized based on your usage data, in compliance with GDPR and CCPA. You can manage your ad preferences in your device settings.
7. Your Rights
You have the right to:
Access:
Request access to the personal data we hold about you.
Correction:
Request corrections to any inaccurate or incomplete data.
Deletion:
Request deletion of your data ("right to be forgotten").
Data Portability:
Request a copy of your data in a structured, commonly used, and machine-readable format.
Objection:
Object to the processing of your data, particularly for direct marketing purposes.
To exercise these rights, please contact our Data Protection Officer at DPO@swipefy.app. We will respond to your request within the timeframe required by applicable laws.
8. Data Protection and Security
We take the security of your data seriously and implement industry-standard measures to protect your information. This includes the use of encryption, secure servers, and regular security audits.
9. Content Moderation
To protect our users, we have systems in place to detect and remove abusive or inappropriate content. This includes both automated and manual moderation processes, in line with Apple App Store and Google Play Store policies.
10. Children’s Privacy
Swipefy is intended for users aged 12 and older. We do not knowingly collect personal information from children under 12. If you believe we have collected information from a child under 12, please contact us immediately at DPO@swipefy.app, and we will take appropriate action in compliance with COPPA (Children's Online Privacy Protection Act) and GDPR.
11. Updates to This Privacy Policy
We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. When we do, we will notify you by email or through the app. Your continued use of Swipefy following any updates signifies your acceptance of the revised Privacy Policy.
12. Contact Information
If you have any questions or concerns about this Privacy Policy, please contact our Data Protection Officer at DPO@swipefy.app.